cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper deals with learning robotic control policies using reinforcement learning, which is a common topic in the robotics community (cs.RO). The use of reinforcement learning to optimize the mapping from states to generalized forces is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also deals with modeling constraints in the equations of motion, which falls under the systems and control category (cs.SY). The use of simulations and real-world data is also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) as these fields often deal with data-driven approaches to learning and modeling.
